<item>
            <title>[HBASE-14522] Document and/or disable hsperfdata GC pauses</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14522</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The JVM by default exports statistics by mmap-ing a file in /tmp (hsperfdata). On Linux, modifying a memory mapped file can block until disk I/O completes, which can be hundreds of milliseconds. Since the JVM modifies these statistics during garbage collection and safepoints, this causes pauses that are hundreds of milliseconds long.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Via &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.evanjones.ca/jvm-mmap-pause.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;JVM mmap pause&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add &lt;tt&gt;-XX:+PerfDisableSharedMem&lt;/tt&gt; to our default options as was apparently done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9242&quot; title=&quot;Add PerfDisableSharedMem to default JVM params&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9242&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9242&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and/or document the presence of this bug so operators know to use tmpfs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hat-tip &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vrodionov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vrodionov&quot;&gt;Vladimir Rodionov&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
